variables.description: Origin information to specify a custom origin.
variables.name: CustomOriginConfig
variables.required: Conditional. You cannot use CustomOriginConfig and                      S3OriginConfig in the same distribution, but you                      must specify one or the other.

variables.description: The DNS name of the Amazon Simple Storage Service (S3) bucket or the HTTP server from which you want                   CloudFront to get objects for this origin.
variables.name: DomainName

variables.description: An identifier for the origin. The value of Id must be unique                   within the distribution.
variables.name: Id

variables.description: The path that CloudFront uses to request content from an S3 bucket or custom origin.                   The combination of the DomainName and OriginPath                   properties must resolve to a valid path. The value must start with a slash mark                      (/) and cannot end with a slash mark.
variables.name: OriginPath

variables.description: Origin information to specify an S3 origin.
variables.name: S3OriginConfig
variables.required: Conditional. You cannot use S3OriginConfig and                      CustomOriginConfig in the same distribution, but you                      must specify one or the other.
